]></dc:creator></item><item><title>He filmed himself for an entire year just to create this moment</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/SYT23Z2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dD9GdMO.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/SYT23Z2</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[J2UDIGI]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The Paradox Of Tolerance</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ChYreg4</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hlVrotZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ChYreg4</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[beardslyyt]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Imigurians have made a new special day...</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/YTT9siQ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rbYDirk.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Story time... 

My grandfather fought in the Pacific in WW2. My great uncle fought in Europe. My GUncle was in one of the units that liberated one of the camps. My dad died when I was 2, both of these men stepped in and became dads to me and my brother. I learned a lot from them.

They rarely talked about their times in the war but when they did I could tell they were still there. My GUncle couldn't talk about when he liberated the camp, when he did he'd just break down and cry and say "never let it happen again". 

I had a job while in college in the Jewish Home for the Aged. Now I'm not Jewish at all, it was a job driving an adult day care bus. But there were camp survivors in that group. I helped care for them. I saw their tattoos, heard their stories, those that would share. 

I'm 57 years old and both men have long passed. They both went on to build lives, my Grandpa had a fleet of combines that would be hired out to harvest. My GUncle was the sheriff of the county next to where my grandparents lived.

The one and only barfight I was in was in my early 20's. I was fresh out of college, back home (grandparent's were always my home) and at a memorial for my GUncle. I was at a bar with friends when a holocaust denier was spouting his bullshit.

I told asked him to stop, it bothered me. Told him my GUncle was there, saw it first hand. He flat out told me to my face my GUncle was a liar and was paid off by the Zionists to lie.

Now, I'm a big guy, built like a brick shithouse (per my Grandpa) but am not a violent person. I'm verbally aggressive and would rather fight with words. But without realizing it was punched this guy. His two friends jumped me and I was there, my friends in shock, trading blows with these 3 guys. Apparently I scared the shit out of my friends, they said it was like I didn't feel it (I didn't at the time, did the day after) and I punch like a steel beam. 

Cops showed up, we were all in cuffs, cop asked me why I started it. I told him why. Turns out he knew my GUncle, worked under him. Told me he'd have done the same. No one was arrested and we were all sent home.

I spent at least 15 years debating people that believed all sorts of nonsense. Was a member of the Skeptic Society for a while. I learned that you can't reason people out of a belief they weren't reasoned into.

Remember:

"The Paradox of Tolerance disappears if you look at tolerance, NOT as a moral standard, but as a social contract. If someone does not abide by the terms of the contract, they are not covered by it. In other words, the intolerant aren't deserving of your tolerance"

Therefore, punch a goddamn Nazi.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/YTT9siQ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MightyUrto]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Nazi punch was deleted immediately, have this instead.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/QgDPV6g</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Ky4jfeV.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/QgDPV6g</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aeonika]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Public Service Announcement!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/2XzTRKV</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ciD3iv7.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tom Morello, Rage Against The Machine, AudioSlave, Prophets of Rage & The Nightwatchmen</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/2XzTRKV</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[thinkybrainpains]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Awesome friends</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/dITGxh2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NeYuIJT.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/dITGxh2</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[theredeemablefemalecousin78]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>the difference flash makes on Noodle's face</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Ew1fiWl</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GVcdd9k.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jA8iTmH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8Z94Kwg.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Ew1fiWl</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[friendlynoodles]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Hand kn